oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena

Class OracleNamedGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.jena.graph.impl.GraphBase
      • oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena.OracleGraphBase
        • oracle.spatial.rdf.client.jena.OracleNamedGraph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.jena.graph.Graph, org.apache.jena.graph.impl.GraphWithPerform

    public class OracleNamedGraph
extends OracleGraphBase
    Represents a named graph backed by an Oracle Semantic Technologies model.

    SPARQL queries against this graph will be limited to the named graph. For example, issuing a wildcard query (i.e. { ?s ?p ?o }) on a Jena model backed by this graph will return all the triples contained within the named graph, but not any triples contained in other graphs that also reside in the same Oracle model.

    The results of issuing a query with GRAPH directives against this graph is undefined. For example, issuing the following query against a Jena model backed by this graph is not supported, 

    
    SELECT ?s ?p ?o
    WHERE {
      GRAPH <urn:some-graph> { ?s ?p ?o }
    }

    All GraphBase methods in this class are limited to the named graph and will not search or affect any other graphs in the underlying Oracle model.

    Since:
    Nov. 2011
